292
00:20:42,266 --> 00:20:44,007
You should ask yourself

293
00:20:44,007 --> 00:20:47,269
why use stylized effects in the first place,

294
00:20:47,269 --> 00:20:50,351
and how will this decision affect your game?

295
00:20:50,351 --> 00:20:52,212
So once you know the answer to that question,

296
00:20:53,152 --> 00:20:57,414
You can ask yourself, is the universe cohesive?

297
00:20:57,414 --> 00:21:00,295
Does everything belong?

298
00:21:00,295 --> 00:21:02,837
If you're going to add a specific effect style

299
00:21:02,837 --> 00:21:06,298
into your games, like I said, does it belong there?

300
00:21:06,298 --> 00:21:13,481
Now, once you're ready to go into the concepting part,

301
00:21:13,481 --> 00:21:16,703
don't be afraid to try new things

302
00:21:16,703 --> 00:21:20,725
and really go wild with the type of effects

303
00:21:20,725 --> 00:21:21,445
that you can create.

304
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:24,409
but also know when to dial it back.

305
00:21:24,409 --> 00:21:27,631
You want to avoid that effects soup look.

306
00:21:27,631 --> 00:21:30,774
And also consider this,

307
00:21:30,774 --> 00:21:33,857
think of effects not only as screen filler

308
00:21:33,857 --> 00:21:37,640
or a way to cover up transitions in animations,

309
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:40,302
but also as a character in itself.

310
00:21:40,302 --> 00:21:42,804
Give them life, give them attitude,

311
00:21:42,804 --> 00:21:44,446
give them personality.

312
